From: Cecilio <ceciliomato@gmail.com>
Date: July 2026
Subject: Nerd-dictation patches for real-time dictation in Spanish

Changes:
1. Block size: 1MB -> 4KB (= 125ms @ 16kHz) for responsive partial results
2. Parec latency: 10ms -> 5ms for lower audio pipeline delay
3. Space between words after pause: when text_prev is reset after a final result,
   prepend a space to the next utterance. The artificial space is NOT stored in
   text_prev so subsequent partial comparisons don't backspace it.
4. Spanish word merging fix: regex that splits short function words (de, con, el,
   la, los, las, en, por, para, que, al, un, una, entre, sobre, hasta, sin, se,
   no, su) from the preceding word when they get merged by VOSK's small model.
5. Debug logging: verbose >= 2 prints raw VOSK output to stderr for debugging.

